Language name: Kharia
Language number: 2301
Alternate names: 
Classification: Austro-Asiatic, Munda
Comments: Kharia is spoken primarily  in Ranchi 
district of Bihar, but also in Raigarh District of Madhya 
Pradesh, Sundargarh District of Orissa, Assam, West 
Bemngal, Andaman and Nicobar Islands.
Voiced plosives are sometimes (pre-)glottalized.

Sources: 

Biligiri, H.S. 1965. Kharia: Phonology, Grammar and 
Vocabulary. Deccan College, Poona.

Pinnow, H-J. 1959. Versuch einer Historischen Lautlehre 
der Kharia-Sprache. Harrassowitz, Wiesbaden.